To start - Upvote, this was some great stuff. I really enjoyed the ambiguity of the potential horror without needing anomalies.

But, this brings up an interesting question. For me, this feels more like a report that would declare these objects non-anomalous, rather than an SCP-EX article.

Nothing of that is a knock to you, this is great writing, but maybe this needs another format. Something like a Proposal for SCP Designation, which was rejected, with a similar format to an SCP article?

I say that, because my feeling is that this object wouldn't have ever actually made it on the list. It never got past the  stage.

Also, bonus points for including a new GoI.







