I once started work on a tale based on this idea. A few excerpts:

+One

-Hide


Item #: PAC-21684

Provisional Object Class: Euclid

Interim Containment Procedures: [Not Yet Defined]

Description: PAC-21684 is , an Estonian daytime soap opera which no one has ever seen. It is broadcast each Monday at 14:00 on the Kanal 1 channel, each episode running for 58 minutes including advertising breaks.

Audience research has consistently failed to find anyone who recalls seeing more than several seconds of the programme. Some remember seeing it mentioned in TV listings, and a few admit to having channel surfed past it.




+Two

-Hide


PAC - and some we just never figure out.




+Three

-Hide


A diamond engagement ring that's been involved in 17 consecutive broken marriages. Anomaly, or sign of the times? PAC-12779, still undetermined.

An infectious but symptomless virus that's been passed among at least 103 people, every one of who eventually dies in a peanut butter related accident. Cosmic joke, or bug in the monitoring software? PAC-10074.

A recipe for root beer that when recited backwards opens a portal to a parallel world ruled by sentient sloths. The recipe is PAC-371, the portal is PAC-371-1 and the world is PAC-371-2. Except it hasn't worked since 1854, so no one's interested in resuming research.

PAC-87855. A woman who has been abducted by at least three serial killers, and each time escaped. The unluckiest woman in the world? The luckiest victim? Generator of serial killers?

PAC-44113. A pair of doors that only let white people unlock them. They used to belong to a golf club.








